The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves using a trainable neural module, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and the use of visual features, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of different features, which can be improved through query-adaptive methods, indicating a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
